&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;Beyond its beauty, the manuscript carries a dramatic history. The original Shi&#8216;i scribe included the line, &#8220;Ali is the beloved of God (&lt;i&gt;&#8216;Ali wali allah&lt;/i&gt;), in his concluding prayer. However, this reference to &apos;Ali, cousin and son in law of Muhammad, and his rightful successor according to Shi&#703;ii Muslims, was covered over in gold paint when the Qur&#8217;an passed from Shi&#8216;i to Sunni hands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
