&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Although initially Kafka viewed himself as a Socialist and rejected the Zionist views of his childhood friend &lt;span style=&quot; color: red;&quot;&gt;S.H. Bergmann&lt;/span&gt;, he deliberated several times, with four of his women partners to immigrate to Palestine! A short while before his death he wrote to Bergmann, who had been in Palestine since 1920, of his plan to visit. The plan never materialized as Kafka&apos;s illness deteriorated rapidly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
