&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;defaultstyle&quot; dir=&quot;LTR&quot;&gt;From a very young age Yahuda mastered both Jewish studies as well as the Arabic language and other European languages. He specialized in classical Arabic literature and at the age of 17 he already published a book on the subject. He then continued his studies in Germany with important scholars in the field of Arabic and Islamic history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt; 
