&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;, serif;&quot;&gt;The miniature makes use of religious symbolism &#8211; Sultan Selim I, on horseback, is dressed in the mantle of the Prophet Muhammad, implying that it is he who defends true Islam, that is, the Sunni tradition. Above him, a flag flies with the legend, &#8220;Victory from Allah and redemption at hand.&#8221; There is no indication that the Shah and his army are Muslims, but rather, they are dressed like pre-Islamic Persian soldiers.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

