&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: -7.1pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;In 2010 a member of the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: red; background: white;&quot;&gt;Hasidut&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: red; background: white;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;of the Gur &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: red; background: white;&quot;&gt;Rebbe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: red; background: white;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;found in his attic an anonymous manuscript. The book was not disposed of previously by his grandfather only because it contained the stamp of the first &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: red; background: white;&quot;&gt;Rebbe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: red; background: white;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;of Radomsk, Rabbi Shlomo Ha-Cohen Rabinowitz (1801-1866). Curious about the value of the manuscript, the grandson contacted a dealer, who in his turn consulted an expert. To his surprise, the expert recognized the distinct writing of De Lonzano, realizing that he was holding a unique and treasured&amp;#160; autograph.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
