&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;defaultstyle&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;Maimonides passed away in 1204 in Egypt and was buried there, but early Jewish tradition claims that he had asked to be buried in the Holy Land and that his boned were brought to burial in Tiberias, where his tomb is still shown.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;defaultstyle&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-family: Arial;&quot;&gt;A very known Hebrew proverb in Maimonides&apos; memory is &quot;From moses to Moses there was none as great as Moses&quot;, meaning that from the biblical Moses to Moses son of Maymon (Maimonides), no one was their match in the leadership of the Jewish people and the knowledge of the Torah. This proverb was inscribed on his grave at Tiberias.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;generator&quot; content=&quot;EditLive! 7.6.2.10&quot; /&gt;
