&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: -7.1pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;The roots of the Kabbalah go back to early esoteric Jewish literature such as the &lt;i&gt;Heavenly Sanctuaries Literature&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;Hekhalot&lt;/i&gt; literature), &lt;i&gt;Work of the Chariot &lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;Ma&apos;aseh Merkava&lt;/i&gt;), &lt;i&gt;The Book of Creation&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;Sefer Yetzira&lt;/i&gt;); this literature itself originates in earlier sources going back to the 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt;-2ed century CE.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
