&lt;p class=&quot;MsoListParagraph&quot; style=&quot; margin-left: 54.0pt; line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black;&quot;&gt;Zweig studied&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophy&quot; title=&quot;Philosophy&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;philosophy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black;&quot;&gt;at the University of Vienna and in 1904 earned a doctoral degree. In those student years Zweig published his first book of poetry, as well as various pieces in the most prestigious newspaper in Vienna, the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neue_Freie_Presse&quot; title=&quot;Neue Freie Presse&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Neue Freie Presse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;whose editor was &lt;span style=&quot; background: lime;&quot;&gt;Theodore Herzl&lt;/span&gt;, the leading figure in the Jewish National Movement&lt;span style=&quot; color: black;&quot;&gt;. Having proven his talent, Zweig was exempted from working in the family business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

