&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: -17.05pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: -7.1pt; line-height: 115%; text-autospace: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;Literally meaning &quot;tradition&quot; or &quot;reception&quot;, Kabbalah is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;the traditional term for the medieval esoteric teachings of Judaism and for Jewish mysticism. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;Although it has much earlier roots, the term Kabbalah &amp;#160;refers usually to the discipline which developed in Provence and &amp;#160;Catalu&#241;a from &amp;#160;the second half of the 12&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; century&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; margin-top: 0cm; margin-right: -17.05pt; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: -7.1pt; line-height: 115%; text-autospace: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;&amp;#160;Following the Jewish expulsion from Spain in 1492, a new trend of the Kabbalah, the Lurianic Kabbalah, developed in Safed, &amp;#160;a town in 16th-century&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Safed&quot; title=&quot;Safed&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; background: white;&quot;&gt;Ottoman Palestine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoHyperlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; background: white;&quot;&gt;, called by the Jews &lt;i&gt;The Land of Israel&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; background: white;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

