&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 12.0pt;&quot;&gt;The Temple of the Ammonite idol Moloch that King Solomon built in the Valley of Gehena (I Kings: 11:7). &amp;#160;According to the Bible (I Kings 16:3; 21:6), the kings of Judah Ahaz and Manasseh took part in the Moloch ritual by passing their sons through the fire. At the bottom, the sawing of the tree where the Prophet Isaiah was hidden by the slaves of the wicked king Manasseh, and Isaiah&apos;s sepulcher are depicted.&amp;#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

