&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top: 4.8pt; margin-right: 0cm; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 14.4pt; background: white;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; color: black;&quot;&gt;On February 22ed 1942 Stefan Zweig and his wife Lotte, having taken an overdose of barbituates, were found dead in their apartment in Petropolis. She was wearing her Kimono, he, wearing his shirt and tie. The previous evening Zweig had played chess with his neighbor, had gone home and written a letter of farewell, explaining his decision to leave the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

