&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; color: black; background: white;&quot;&gt;After graduating in 1906 and completing his year of training, Kafka started to work as an insurance officer.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#160; Kafka called this his &lt;i&gt;Brotberuf&lt;/i&gt; or &quot;Bread Job&quot;, and constantly bemoaned the fact that he did not have enough time for his real passion: writing. Despite this he wrote almost incessantly, writing stories, novels and letters. Yet, he was extremely critical regarding his works; as a result, many of his texts remained unfinished. Thus, his three famous novels, &lt;i&gt;The Castle&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;The Trial&lt;/i&gt;, &lt;i&gt;The Missing Man&lt;/i&gt;, as well as a number of stories were found unfinished by his close friend, the writer Max Brod. One of the most famous stories is &lt;i&gt;The Metamorphosis&lt;/i&gt;, relating the story of the miserable Gregor Samsa who woke up one morning finding himself transformed into a huge insect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&#160;&lt;/b&gt;Besides being a brilliant scientist and theologian, Newton was also displayed adroit skills as an administrator. In 1696 He was appointed Warden of the Royal Mint in London. In this capacity Newton wrote this letter to the tin mine owners, explaining to them through meticulous calculations that Her Majesty, Queen Anne, has already purchased from them much more tin than she can sell, leaving her with &quot;dead stock&quot; (surplus), which can only be sold at a loss.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;DefaultStyle&quot;&gt;He therefore announces his decision to end the contract with them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

