&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;LTR&quot;&gt;Between&amp;#160;1914-1922 Yahuda served as professor in Madrid. (In later years Yahuda wrote memoirs in Hebrew describing&amp;#160; his sojourn in Spain.) He then left Spain, and spent the years between 1922 and 1942 travelling all over Europe and the East. During these years Yahuda acquired many rare manuscripts and traded in them. Yahuda&apos;s great erudition in many fields, and especially in Islam, explains the superior manuscripts that he chose to acquire during his travels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

&lt;!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd&quot;&gt;&lt;html xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;&gt;
